<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1410,1876]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,1490,1516]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
. The small specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[631,812,1490,1516]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
agrees well with the material on hand of 
<taxonomicName box="[1293,1436,1491,1516]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Kaikoura, 
<collectingCountry box="[451,612,1530,1556]" name="New Zealand" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[622,883,1531,1556]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis box="[622,883,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Petrolisthes elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is allied to 
<taxonomicName box="[1019,1161,1531,1556]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1019,1161,1531,1556]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(de Haan, 
<number box="[1289,1351,1530,1556]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1849.0">1849</number>
), but is distinguished by the median lobe of the rostrum being more strongly produced forward, median lobe of the third thoracic sternite being comparatively higher, third segment of the antennal peduncle with a small spine on the median anterior margin, dactyl of the larger cheliped with a rounded tooth on the median cutting region, and comparatively stouter ambulatory legs with dactyli each armed with four corneous spines (three spines in 
<taxonomicName box="[261,404,1731,1756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[261,404,1731,1756]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1410,1876]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,1770,1796]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[368,529,1770,1796]" name="New Zealand" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, Tasmania, and some indefinite records from “coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1187,1301,1770,1796]" name="Australia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Australia</collectingCountry>
”; occurring intertidally and in shallow water down to 
<quantity box="[639,728,1810,1836]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="m" value="12.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="5.0">5–20 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haig" box="[743,872,1810,1836]" pageId="21" pageNumber="46" refString="Haig, J. (1964) Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 1916. 81. Porcellanid crabs from the Indo- West Pacific, Part I. Videnskabelige Meddelelser Dansk Naturhistrisk Forening i Kj g benhavn, 126, 355 - 386." type="journal article" year="1964">
Haig 
<number box="[809,872,1810,1836]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of the species from outside of 
<collectingCountry box="[237,394,1850,1876]" name="New Zealand" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[451,562,1850,1876]" name="Australia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
